The main differences between Python and JavaScript programming languages are: 
- Python is a general-purpose programming language, while JavaScript is a multi-purpose language used for client-side scripting; 
- Python is an interpreted language, while JavaScript is a compiled language; 
- Python has static typing, while JavaScript has dynamic typing; 
- Python is considered a “high-level” language, while JavaScript is a “low-level” language; 
- Python has a huge standard library, while JavaScript has a small standard library; 
- Python is object-oriented, while JavaScript is event-driven; 
- Python has a curly-brace syntax, while JavaScript has a JavaScript-specific syntax.

#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

using namespace std;

int main()
{
    ifstream inFile;
    string word = "wonderful";
    int count = 0;

    inFile.open("filename.txt");
    if (inFile.good())
    {
        while (getline(inFile, word))
        {
            count++;
        }
        inFile.close();
    }
    cout << count << endl;
}

